 Stoke War Hospit Stoke On Trent 17/8 /16 [ Note appear on the top of this letter ? Will send Parcel under regist Post . C. ] Dear J. I hope that you receiv my cabl safe , it should have left on the 5th of Inst I have done veri littl write sinc I came here as it make my arm ach after I have been at it for awhil , I can onli write veri slowli but in a coupl of week thing will be veri differ , as the wound is heal up nice of cours it will be some time befor I will be back with the boy as the muscl will be stiff for awhil , The rotten part of the busi is that I had a return of a sort of fever which I had an attack of when in the trench in June my temperatur was normal and when the fever came on jump to 103.6 . the nurs thought that I was up to some joke so took my temp . again and found that I was not . next morn I was still feverish so had to stay in bed . I had a good rest certain but yesterday was the first day that I was allow up for a fortnight I have been truss up like an Invalid
